<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hot and cold • hot and hot</xh5><p> <i>hot and cold—</i>short for “hot and cold water” (in a hotel, etc.): He’s working out that plan for laying on <u>hot and cold</u>. </p><p><i>hot and hot—</i>said of dishes served in succession as soon as cooked: Her potato cakes came in <u>hot and hot</u> from a potoven.</p> </entry>
